                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d705">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/2392</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Secretary of State</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-03-15">March 15,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Ambassador<note n="35" xml:id="d705fn35">The French Ambassador, Gaston
                        Henry-Haye.</note> called at his request. He said that health conditions in
                    Syria were very bad and that his Government desired that this Government request
                    the cooperation of Great Britain to permit medical products from the United
                    States to be sent to Syria and Lebanon. I replied that I would be glad to take
                    this matter up with the British.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>C[<hi rend="smallcaps">ordell</hi>] H[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >ull</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
